Don&#39;t use sed to edit XML, use an XML-aware tool. For example, in [xsh](http://metacpan.org/pod/distribution/XML-XSH2/xsh) you can write

    register-namespace pom http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 ;
    
    $pom         = $ARGV[1] ;
    $old_version = $ARGV[2] ;
    $new_version = $ARGV[3] ;
    
    open $pom ;
    for //pom:version[. = $old_version]
        set . $new_version ;
    save :b ;

 Seems you want increasing number in a column, do a try:

    //execute 
    SET @val := 0;

    //update 
    UPDATE test SET id = ( SELECT @val := @val + 1 ) ORDER BY id;

