You can use useEffect hook. Below is an example:

    const todo = () =&gt; {
    	useEffect(() =&gt; {
    		&lt;api calls&gt;
    	}, [ &lt;value to be watched&gt; ] );       
    }

Whenever value to be watched changes, the first argument (i.e. arrow function above) gets executed.

Let&#39;s say you want the api calls to get executed only once, in that case keep values to be watched as empty. And you are good to go.

